description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for highly motivated and dynamic nurses to join our friendly and experienced Community Mental Health Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We welcome applications from nurses who have a strong commitment to delivering high quality, safe and compassionate care and a proven ability to provide comprehensive assessments and interventions for adults of working age with a range of acute functional illnesses. Excellent interpersonal and organizational skills are essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will receive supervision, support and training to develop your skills within this post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a permanent full time post of 37.5 hours per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Employment in this post requires an Enhanced Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS) check. The DBS levies a charge of £40 and the Trust will recover this cost in instalments from your first 3 salary payments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants who subscribe to the DBS update service and are able to present a valid DBS certificate will not incur a charge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Adrian Rendall Job title: Team Leader&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: adrian.rendall1@nhs.net Telephone number: 01202 584440&lt;/p&gt;
